SAINT STEVEN : A CLOSE ENCOUNTER OF THE SPIELBERG KIND Steven
Spielberg, master of sharks and dinosaurs, has celebrated a new
triumpth with his latest film. ``Saving Private Ryan'' not only
symbolizes Americans' struggle with their recent history -- and is
the first of several new World War II films now in the making -- it
also reflects the director's own struggle with the shadows of his
personal past. From Der Spiegel. 2,000 words. (English translation
available.) Please fax to Paris 33.1.47.42.80.44 or
