<P>
   POPE-LIBERALS (Undated) _ One hundred and forty liberal Catholic
groups worldwide have issued a statement saying what the next pope
should be like. The statement, sent to all members of the College
of Cardinals, is evidence of a convergence of liberal groups as
they anticipate the death of the Pope John Paul II. It is also
evidence of the growing importance of liberal Catholics in Europe,
who are the major backers of the liberal agenda. They want a pope
that is more democratic who will not crack down on dissidents. They
also think women should be priests and celibacy should be optional.
By Gustav Niebuhr.
</P>
<P>
   WYO-GAY-BEATING (Denver) _ Profiles of the two men, Aaron
McKinney, 22, and Russell A. Henderson, 21, accused of beating and
killing Matthew Shepard, the gay University of Wyoming freshman.
Both are dropouts from Laramie High School. One lives in a trailer
with his girlfriend, with whom he had a child. When his mother died
five years ago, he saw the doctor in a bar and beat him up. One has
a burglary record and worked at Taco Bell. By James Brooke.
</P>
<P>
