earnings fell 50 percent in the third quarter, to 50 cents a share
_ well below the 90 cents a share that analysts had expected. Net
was 21 cents a share, reflecting charges related to the Nationsbank
merger _ and a $372 million charge-off related to its investment in
D.E. Shaw. The bank's shares fall 13 percent. Separately, First
Union's operating earnings rose 35 percent as the bank boosted its
investment-management income. And Bank Boston cuts its
emerging-markets staff. By Timothy L. O'Brien.
