grappling with the question of whether to keep objectionable
material on the Internet from reaching computers intended for
public use, and, for those libraries that have decided on. After
much soul-searching, the Austin library installed filtering
software on most of its computers, a decision that divided the
community, as it has many others. By Katie Hafner.
